    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "FYI, the reasoning behind have `testnet` be create-only is that if you want it to also resume, then you probably want to check that the values supplied are the same as what it was created with (e.g., genesis time, validator count, etc). Otherwise you end up thinking you have `testnet quick 12 1234` but you're actually running `testnet recent 100` from a few days ago.\r\n\r\nChecking that the parameters are the same involves loading the beacon state from disk and analyzing it before booting and this is not already in our flow. In other words, it requires non-trivial logic that only applies to testnets.",
